Portugal Opposition Party’s Lead Widens in Poll, Expresso Says

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-04-01T06:48:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/portugal-opposition-party-s-lead-widens-in-poll-expresso-says.html
Portugal ’s Social Democrats, the
biggest opposition party, led the ruling Socialist Party of
Portuguese Prime Minister Jose Socrates by a wider margin in a
survey of voters’ intentions for parliamentary elections,
Expresso reported on its website.  The survey indicated 37.3 percent backing from voters for
the  Social Democratic Party  led by Pedro Passos Coelho, 0.4
percentage point more than in a previous survey, the weekly
newspaper said. The survey indicated 30.4 percent support for
the Socialists, 0.2 percentage point less than in the previous
poll, according to Expresso.  The survey published today was carried out by Eurosondagem
SA from March 27 to 30 and 1,021 telephone interviews were
carried out, Expresso said. The margin of error is 3.07 percent,
the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
